# Testing Rules

- Add or update tests for changed behavior when a test framework already exists.
- Prefer focused tests over broad snapshot tests.
- Do not weaken existing tests to pass.
- After changes, mention the exact test command to run.
- If unable to run tests, say so and explain what should be verified manually.
- Cover edge cases, invalid input, and permission failures where relevant.